MODEL: opus

Prevent Boss from ever again mistaking an idle pane for an active one. Root cause: ctx% in the tmux status bar was used as an activity signal — it's not. Idle panes at the ❯ prompt can have any ctx%.

MUST QUEUE BEHIND TASK 551 — 551 is touching .claude/hooks/, shell/, CLAUDE.md, agents/. Do not start until 551 Phase 3 integration commits.

THREE DELIVERABLES:

1. Canonical activity signal — new Go subcommand 'doey-ctl status observe <pane>' (or equivalent shell tool) that returns structured JSON:
   {
     active: bool,
     indicator: 'Sketching'|'Running'|'Cogitated'|'thinking'|'idle'|null,
     ctx_pct: N,
     last_output_age_sec: N,
     status_file_age_sec: N,
     heartbeat_age_sec: N | null
   }
   Logic: active = (spinner glyph found in last 30 pane lines) OR (status==BUSY AND updated_at < 10s ago) OR (heartbeat < 15s ago).
   Spinner glyphs to detect: ✻ ● ⎿ with verbs Sketching|Running|Cogitated|Baked|Sautéed|Brewed|Cooked|Thinking|Frolicking|Crystallizing|etc. Use a regex matching the standard Claude Code spinner format.
   Capture at least 30 lines, not 4.

2. Worker heartbeat — minimal PostToolUse hook addition that touches /tmp/doey/doey/heartbeat/<pane_safe>.heartbeat on every tool call. File mtime = last activity. Zero overhead. Existing hooks should be extended, not new files created if avoidable.

3. Boss protocol update in CLAUDE.md (STATUS CHECK PROTOCOL section) and agents/doey-boss.md:
   - Add explicit rule: 'ctx% is NOT an activity signal — ignore it for activity determination'
   - List spinner indicators Boss should look for
   - Require minimum 20-line capture for status checks (not 4)
   - Point Boss at 'doey-ctl status observe' as the preferred tool when available
   - Define the idle signature: pane ends with ❯ prompt and no trailing spinner

4. Boss memory file at /home/doey/.claude/agent-memory/doey-boss/feedback_status_signals.md — user-level memory, not project file. Content: the rule above plus the why (user corrected me on this). Also add index line to /home/doey/.claude/agent-memory/doey-boss/MEMORY.md.

VERIFICATION:
- go build ./... in tui/ must PASS
- tests/test-bash-compat.sh must PASS
- Manual test: run 'doey-ctl status observe 2.0' against a known-busy pane → active:true. Against a known-idle pane → active:false.
- Commit per deliverable.

DO NOT touch anything task 551 is touching until 551 lands.
